      "source_ref": "experience:ge-healthcare",
      "source_title": "GE HealthCare — Software Engineer II — Platform Engineering",
      "text": "Software Engineer II — Platform Engineering at GE HealthCare (Aug 2025 — Present). Platform services behind mission-critical diagnostic imaging workflows: high-volume device telemetry, real-time ingestion, and downstream clinical integrations. Architected Kafka event streaming for device telemetry — 120K+ msgs/sec sustained at sub-100ms p99 Cut end-to-end pipeline latency 38% with an async FastAPI refactor and a Redis caching layer Instrumented tracing across 6 services with OpenTelemetry + Datadog — 52% faster incident detection Shipped LangChain summarization in the clinical report pipeline — 20% less radiologist review time Stack: Python, FastAPI, Kafka, Redis, AWS EKS, Kubernetes, Helm, OpenTelemetry, Datadog.",
